currentDoc:
Are We Being Bad Citizens If We Don't Keep Up With the News?

In your opinion, are we being bad citizens if we don't keep up with the news? Do you think all people have some responsibility to know what is going on in the world? Does engaging with current events actually do anything at all? Why do you think the way you do?

---

In my opinion,

currentSuggestions.original: That being said, I don't think it's everyone's job to keep up with every little bit of gossip in every one of our nation's 50
currentSuggestions.trimmed: That being said, I don't think it's everyone's job to keep up with every little bit of gossip in every one of our nation's 50

currentSuggestions.original: I would be disappointed in myself, if I didn't make any effort to stay away from the crosshairs.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I would be disappointed in myself, if I didn't make any effort to stay away from the crosshairs.

currentSuggestions.original: For example, knowing what a candidate believes about abortion is very important to me, so I try to read up on it.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: For example, knowing what a candidate believes about abortion is very important to me, so I try to read up on it.

currentSuggestions.original: It's okay to take a break from the news once in awhile.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: It's okay to take a break from the news once in awhile.

currentSuggestions.original: Information, provided people actually take the time to learn from it, is terribly empowering.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Information, provided people actually take the time to learn from it, is terribly empowering.

ops.insert: Information, provided people actually take the time to learn from it, is terribly empowering.

currentSuggestions.original: Related to this, people should have a basic understanding of some of the issues going on in the world.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Related to this, people should have a basic understanding of some of the issues going on in the world.

currentSuggestions.original: And, I think all of us should be making informed decisions, regardless of whether or not we engage with politics.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: And, I think all of us should be making informed decisions, regardless of whether or not we engage with politics.

currentSuggestions.original: What we vote is our business, unless it becomes the public's business.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: What we vote is our business, unless it becomes the public's business.

currentSuggestions.original: Ignorance is a terrible thing.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Ignorance is a terrible thing.

currentSuggestions.original: If we don't, we aren't truly participating in the democratic process.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: If we don't, we aren't truly participating in the democratic process.

ops.insert: If we don't, we aren't truly participating in the democratic process.

currentSuggestions.original: The recent election in the US taught us that it's difficult to determine what information is really true and what's just one person's opinion.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: The recent election in the US taught us that it's difficult to determine what information is really true and what's just one person's opinion.

currentSuggestions.original: In order to claim that you are informed, you would have to try and consume as much information as possible, but even this is difficult.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: In order to claim that you are informed, you would have to try and consume as much information as possible, but even this is difficult.

currentSuggestions.original: We are left thinking that our world is a much more dangerous place than it actually is.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: We are left thinking that our world is a much more dangerous place than it actually is.

currentSuggestions.original: We have to sift through mountains of detail in order to find what we need.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: We have to sift through mountains of detail in order to find what we need.

currentSuggestions.original: It's difficult, but not impossible.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: It's difficult, but not impossible.

ops.insert: The recent election in the US taught us that it's difficult to determine what information is really true and what's just one person's opinion.

currentSuggestions.original: My personal resolution for this year is going to be to spend, at minimum, 10 minutes a day, checking a publication that interests me.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: My personal resolution for this year is going to be to spend, at minimum, 10 minutes a day, checking a publication that interests me.

currentSuggestions.original: People are so divided on what they actually want, how we can come together within our country, and what the world will be like in 20 years -
currentSuggestions.trimmed: People are so divided on what they actually want, how we can come together within our country, and what the world will be like in 20 years -

currentSuggestions.original: This is complicated even more when you add in all of the texts, tweets, e-mails, and facebook feeds that fill up a person's news
currentSuggestions.trimmed: This is complicated even more when you add in all of the texts, tweets, e-mails, and facebook feeds that fill up a person's news

currentSuggestions.original: The process of following the news isn't always easy.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: The process of following the news isn't always easy.

currentSuggestions.original: Still, if you don't follow the news, I think you are missing out on some great stories.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Still, if you don't follow the news, I think you are missing out on some great stories.

ops.insert: This is complicated even more when you add in all of the texts, tweets, e-mails, and facebook feeds that fill up a person's news

currentSuggestions.original: How can anyone be expected to keep up?
currentSuggestions.trimmed: How can anyone be expected to keep up?

currentSuggestions.original: Even if people try to stay up-to-date, the sheer amount of news out there seems to be overwhelming.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Even if people try to stay up-to-date, the sheer amount of news out there seems to be overwhelming.

currentSuggestions.original: I think that we all have a social responsibility to just stay informed on what's going on in the world.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I think that we all have a social responsibility to just stay informed on what's going on in the world.

currentSuggestions.original: And has it really done anything?
currentSuggestions.trimmed: And has it really done anything?

currentSuggestions.original: Is this article bias?
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Is this article bias?

ops.insert: Even if people try to stay up-to-date, the sheer amount of news out there seems to be overwhelming.

currentSuggestions.original: Knowing the difference between these sources is sometimes difficult.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Knowing the difference between these sources is sometimes difficult.

currentSuggestions.original: We also don't seem to differentiate between authoritative news sources, and the internet blogs of anonymous people.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: We also don't seem to differentiate between authoritative news sources, and the internet blogs of anonymous people.

currentSuggestions.original: We've lost the line between what's factual and what's not, and as a result, everyone has become distrustful of some information.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: We've lost the line between what's factual and what's not, and as a result, everyone has become distrustful of some information.

currentSuggestions.original: In this day and age, news organizations are trying to fill the voids left behind by decline of investigative journalism.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: In this day and age, news organizations are trying to fill the voids left behind by decline of investigative journalism.

currentSuggestions.original: Honestly, even mainstream news doesn't always tell it like it is.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Honestly, even mainstream news doesn't always tell it like it is.

ops.insert: In this day and age, news organizations are trying to fill the voids left behind by decline of investigative journalism.

currentSuggestions.original: Without the proper information, we can't participate in our society in a meaningful way.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Without the proper information, we can't participate in our society in a meaningful way.

currentSuggestions.original: This has led to an education system that isn't very focused on the state of the world.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: This has led to an education system that isn't very focused on the state of the world.

currentSuggestions.original: This has left many people in the US without the ability to critically think about the world they live in.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: This has left many people in the US without the ability to critically think about the world they live in.

currentSuggestions.original: Somewhere in there, the definition of good citizenship hasn't been changing with the times.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Somewhere in there, the definition of good citizenship hasn't been changing with the times.

ops.insert: This has left many people in the US without the ability to critically think about the world they live in.

currentSuggestions.original: It doesn't take long for groups to take the news and create their own negative narrative around it.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: It doesn't take long for groups to take the news and create their own negative narrative around it.

currentSuggestions.original: If we actively seek out the truth, but hold on to our skepticism, it doesn't matter if we don't catch every piece of news.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: If we actively seek out the truth, but hold on to our skepticism, it doesn't matter if we don't catch every piece of news.

currentSuggestions.original: Life can be complicated and as a person, we need to define our own personal boundaries.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Life can be complicated and as a person, we need to define our own personal boundaries.

currentSuggestions.original: Now, more than ever, before we're able to bring about meaningful change to our society, we have to know exactly where the issues lie.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Now, more than ever, before we're able to bring about meaningful change to our society, we have to know exactly where the issues lie.

ops.insert: If we actively seek out the truth, but hold on to our skepticism, it doesn't matter if we don't catch every piece of news.
